SIMPLE: underwing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underwing
<hw>Un"der*wing`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the posterior wings of an
insect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of
noctuid moths belonging to <gen>Catocala</gen> and allied genera, in
which the hind wings are banded with red and black or other conspicuous
colors. Many of the species are called <stype>red
underwing</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underwitted</ent>⟦br⟧
